Thousands of troops were deployed to Baluchistan after a rocket attack on a gas plant killed eight people.
Tribal rebels attacked a paramilitary convoy, resulting in three soldiers dead and seven injured.
The rebels used light and heavy weapons, firing over 150 rockets and mortar shells.
The government dismissed claims of up to 50 tribesmen killed.
Fierce gun battles between tribal rebels and Pakistani troops left 30 dead and 70 injured.
The violence escalated after a doctor's rape at the gas field.
Thousands fled their homes due to threats, and bomb blasts caused further chaos in the region.
